{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Erez Lieberman Aiden: Everyone knows"},{"time":2000,"text":"that a picture is worth a thousand words."},{"time":7000,"text":"But we at Harvard"},{"time":9000,"text":"were wondering if this was really true."},{"time":12000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":14000,"text":"So we assembled a team of experts,"},{"time":18000,"text":"spanning Harvard, MIT,"},{"time":20000,"text":"The American Heritage Dictionary, The Encyclopedia Britannica"},{"time":23000,"text":"and even our proud sponsors,"},{"time":25000,"text":"the Google."},{"time":28000,"text":"And we cogitated about this"},{"time":30000,"text":"for about four years."},{"time":32000,"text":"And we came to a startling conclusion."},{"time":37000,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen, a picture is not worth a thousand words."},{"time":40000,"text":"In fact, we found some pictures"},{"time":42000,"text":"that are worth 500 billion words."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47000,"text":"Jean-Baptiste Michel: So how did we get to this conclusion?"},{"time":49000,"text":"So Erez and I were thinking about ways"},{"time":51000,"text":"to get a big picture of human culture"},{"time":53000,"text":"and human history: change over time."},{"time":56000,"text":"So many books actually have been written over the years."},{"time":58000,"text":"So we were thinking, well the best way to learn from them"},{"time":60000,"text":"is to read all of these millions of books."},{"time":62000,"text":"Now of course, if there's a scale for how awesome that is,"},{"time":65000,"text":"that has to rank extremely, extremely high."},{"time":68000,"text":"Now the problem is there's an X-axis for that,"},{"time":70000,"text":"which is the practical axis."},{"time":72000,"text":"This is very, very low."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":77000,"text":"Now people tend to use an alternative approach,"},{"time":80000,"text":"which is to take a few sources and read them very carefully."},{"time":82000,"text":"This is extremely practical, but not so awesome."},{"time":84000,"text":"What you really want to do"},{"time":87000,"text":"is to get to the awesome yet practical part of this space."},{"time":90000,"text":"So it turns out there was a company across the river called Google"},{"time":93000,"text":"who had started a digitization project a few years back"},{"time":95000,"text":"that might just enable this approach."},{"time":97000,"text":"They have digitized millions of books."},{"time":99000,"text":"So what that means is, one could use computational methods"},{"time":102000,"text":"to read all of the books in a click of a button."},{"time":104000,"text":"That's very practical and extremely awesome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108000,"text":"ELA: Let me tell you a little bit about where books come from."},{"time":110000,"text":"Since time immemorial, there have been authors."},{"time":113000,"text":"These authors have been striving to write books."},{"time":116000,"text":"And this became considerably easier"},{"time":118000,"text":"with the development of the printing press some centuries ago."},{"time":120000,"text":"Since then, the authors have won"},{"time":123000,"text":"on 129 million distinct occasions,"},{"time":125000,"text":"publishing books."},{"time":127000,"text":"Now if those books are not lost to history,"},{"time":129000,"text":"then they are somewhere in a library,"},{"time":131000,"text":"and many of those books have been getting retrieved from the libraries"},{"time":134000,"text":"and digitized by Google,"},{"time":136000,"text":"which has scanned 15 million books to date."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138000,"text":"Now when Google digitizes a book, they put it into a really nice format."},{"time":141000,"text":"Now we've got the data, plus we have metadata."},{"time":143000,"text":"We have information about things like where was it published,"},{"time":146000,"text":"who was the author, when was it published."},{"time":148000,"text":"And what we do is go through all of those records"},{"time":151000,"text":"and exclude everything that's not the highest quality data."},{"time":155000,"text":"What we're left with"},{"time":157000,"text":"is a collection of five million books,"},{"time":160000,"text":"500 billion words,"},{"time":163000,"text":"a string of characters a thousand times longer"},{"time":165000,"text":"than the human genome --"},{"time":168000,"text":"a text which, when written out,"},{"time":170000,"text":"would stretch from here to the Moon and back"},{"time":172000,"text":"10 times over --"},{"time":174000,"text":"a veritable shard of our cultural genome."},{"time":178000,"text":"Of course what we did"},{"time":180000,"text":"when faced with such outrageous hyperbole ..."},{"time":183000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":185000,"text":"was what any self-respecting researchers"},{"time":188000,"text":"would have done."},{"time":191000,"text":"We took a page out of XKCD,"},{"time":193000,"text":"and we said, \"Stand back."},{"time":195000,"text":"We're going to try science.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":197000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":199000,"text":"JM: Now of course, we were thinking,"},{"time":201000,"text":"well let's just first put the data out there"},{"time":203000,"text":"for people to do science to it."},{"time":205000,"text":"Now we're thinking, what data can we release?"},{"time":207000,"text":"Well of course, you want to take the books"},{"time":209000,"text":"and release the full text of these five million books."},{"time":211000,"text":"Now Google, and Jon Orwant in particular,"},{"time":213000,"text":"told us a little equation that we should learn."},{"time":215000,"text":"So you have five million, that is, five million authors"},{"time":218000,"text":"and five million plaintiffs is a massive lawsuit."},{"time":221000,"text":"So, although that would be really, really awesome,"},{"time":223000,"text":"again, that's extremely, extremely impractical."},{"time":226000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":228000,"text":"Now again, we kind of caved in,"},{"time":230000,"text":"and we did the very practical approach, which was a bit less awesome."},{"time":233000,"text":"We said, well instead of releasing the full text,"},{"time":235000,"text":"we're going to release statistics about the books."},{"time":237000,"text":"So take for instance \"A gleam of happiness.\""},{"time":239000,"text":"It's four words; we call that a four-gram."},{"time":241000,"text":"We're going to tell you how many times a particular four-gram"},{"time":243000,"text":"appeared in books in 1801, 1802, 1803,"},{"time":245000,"text":"all the way up to 2008."},{"time":247000,"text":"That gives us a time series"},{"time":249000,"text":"of how frequently this particular sentence was used over time."},{"time":251000,"text":"We do that for all the words and phrases that appear in those books,"},{"time":254000,"text":"and that gives us a big table of two billion lines"},{"time":257000,"text":"that tell us about the way culture has been changing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259000,"text":"ELA: So those two billion lines,"},{"time":261000,"text":"we call them two billion n-grams."},{"time":263000,"text":"What do they tell us?"},{"time":265000,"text":"Well the individual n-grams measure cultural trends."},{"time":267000,"text":"Let me give you an example."},{"time":269000,"text":"Let's suppose that I am thriving,"},{"time":271000,"text":"then tomorrow I want to tell you about how well I did."},{"time":273000,"text":"And so I might say, \"Yesterday, I throve.\""},{"time":276000,"text":"Alternatively, I could say, \"Yesterday, I thrived.\""},{"time":279000,"text":"Well which one should I use?"},{"time":282000,"text":"How to know?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":284000,"text":"As of about six months ago,"},{"time":286000,"text":"the state of the art in this field"},{"time":288000,"text":"is that you would, for instance,"},{"time":290000,"text":"go up to the following psychologist with fabulous hair,"},{"time":292000,"text":"and you'd say,"},{"time":294000,"text":"\"Steve, you're an expert on the irregular verbs."},{"time":297000,"text":"What should I do?\""},{"time":299000,"text":"And he'd tell you, \"Well most people say thrived,"},{"time":301000,"text":"but some people say throve.\""},{"time":304000,"text":"And you also knew, more or less,"},{"time":306000,"text":"that if you were to go back in time 200 years"},{"time":309000,"text":"and ask the following statesman with equally fabulous hair,"},{"time":312000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":315000,"text":"\"Tom, what should I say?\""},{"time":317000,"text":"He'd say, \"Well, in my day, most people throve,"},{"time":319000,"text":"but some thrived.\""},{"time":322000,"text":"So now what I'm just going to show you is raw data."},{"time":324000,"text":"Two rows from this table of two billion entries."},{"time":328000,"text":"What you're seeing is year by year frequency"},{"time":330000,"text":"of \"thrived\" and \"throve\" over time."},{"time":334000,"text":"Now this is just two"},{"time":336000,"text":"out of two billion rows."},{"time":339000,"text":"So the entire data set"},{"time":341000,"text":"is a billion times more awesome than this slide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":346000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":350000,"text":"JM: Now there are many other pictures that are worth 500 billion words."},{"time":352000,"text":"For instance, this one."},{"time":354000,"text":"If you just take influenza,"},{"time":356000,"text":"you will see peaks at the time where you knew"},{"time":358000,"text":"big flu epidemics were killing people around the globe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361000,"text":"ELA: If you were not yet convinced,"},{"time":364000,"text":"sea levels are rising,"},{"time":366000,"text":"so is atmospheric CO2 and global temperature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369000,"text":"JM: You might also want to have a look at this particular n-gram,"},{"time":372000,"text":"and that's to tell Nietzsche that God is not dead,"},{"time":375000,"text":"although you might agree that he might need a better publicist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":380000,"text":"ELA: You can get at some pretty abstract concepts with this sort of thing."},{"time":383000,"text":"For instance, let me tell you the history"},{"time":385000,"text":"of the year 1950."},{"time":387000,"text":"Pretty much for the vast majority of history,"},{"time":389000,"text":"no one gave a damn about 1950."},{"time":391000,"text":"In 1700, in 1800, in 1900,"},{"time":393000,"text":"no one cared."},{"time":397000,"text":"Through the 30s and 40s,"},{"time":399000,"text":"no one cared."},{"time":401000,"text":"Suddenly, in the mid-40s,"},{"time":403000,"text":"there started to be a buzz."},{"time":405000,"text":"People realized that 1950 was going to happen,"},{"time":407000,"text":"and it could be big."},{"time":409000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":412000,"text":"But nothing got people interested in 1950"},{"time":415000,"text":"like the year 1950."},{"time":418000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":421000,"text":"People were walking around obsessed."},{"time":423000,"text":"They couldn't stop talking"},{"time":425000,"text":"about all the things they did in 1950,"},{"time":428000,"text":"all the things they were planning to do in 1950,"},{"time":431000,"text":"all the dreams of what they wanted to accomplish in 1950."},{"time":436000,"text":"In fact, 1950 was so fascinating"},{"time":438000,"text":"that for years thereafter,"},{"time":440000,"text":"people just kept talking about all the amazing things that happened,"},{"time":443000,"text":"in '51, '52, '53."},{"time":445000,"text":"Finally in 1954,"},{"time":447000,"text":"someone woke up and realized"},{"time":449000,"text":"that 1950 had gotten somewhat pass√©."},{"time":453000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":455000,"text":"And just like that, the bubble burst."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":459000,"text":"And the story of 1950"},{"time":461000,"text":"is the story of every year that we have on record,"},{"time":463000,"text":"with a little twist, because now we've got these nice charts."},{"time":466000,"text":"And because we have these nice charts, we can measure things."},{"time":469000,"text":"We can say, \"Well how fast does the bubble burst?\""},{"time":471000,"text":"And it turns out that we can measure that very precisely."},{"time":474000,"text":"Equations were derived, graphs were produced,"},{"time":477000,"text":"and the net result"},{"time":479000,"text":"is that we find that the bubble bursts faster and faster"},{"time":482000,"text":"with each passing year."},{"time":484000,"text":"We are losing interest in the past more rapidly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489000,"text":"JM: Now a little piece of career advice."},{"time":491000,"text":"So for those of you who seek to be famous,"},{"time":493000,"text":"we can learn from the 25 most famous political figures,"},{"time":495000,"text":"authors, actors and so on."},{"time":497000,"text":"So if you want to become famous early on, you should be an actor,"},{"time":500000,"text":"because then fame starts rising by the end of your 20s --"},{"time":502000,"text":"you're still young, it's really great."},{"time":504000,"text":"Now if you can wait a little bit, you should be an author,"},{"time":506000,"text":"because then you rise to very great heights,"},{"time":508000,"text":"like Mark Twain, for instance: extremely famous."},{"time":510000,"text":"But if you want to reach the very top,"},{"time":512000,"text":"you should delay gratification"},{"time":514000,"text":"and, of course, become a politician."},{"time":516000,"text":"So here you will become famous by the end of your 50s,"},{"time":518000,"text":"and become very, very famous afterward."},{"time":520000,"text":"So scientists also tend to get famous when they're much older."},{"time":523000,"text":"Like for instance, biologists and physics"},{"time":525000,"text":"tend to be almost as famous as actors."},{"time":527000,"text":"One mistake you should not do is become a mathematician."},{"time":530000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":532000,"text":"If you do that,"},{"time":534000,"text":"you might think, \"Oh great. I'm going to do my best work when I'm in my 20s.\""},{"time":537000,"text":"But guess what, nobody will really care."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":542000,"text":"ELA: There are more sobering notes"},{"time":544000,"text":"among the n-grams."},{"time":546000,"text":"For instance, here's the trajectory of Marc Chagall,"},{"time":548000,"text":"an artist born in 1887."},{"time":550000,"text":"And this looks like the normal trajectory of a famous person."},{"time":553000,"text":"He gets more and more and more famous,"},{"time":557000,"text":"except if you look in German."},{"time":559000,"text":"If you look in German, you see something completely bizarre,"},{"time":561000,"text":"something you pretty much never see,"},{"time":563000,"text":"which is he becomes extremely famous"},{"time":565000,"text":"and then all of a sudden plummets,"},{"time":567000,"text":"going through a nadir between 1933 and 1945,"},{"time":570000,"text":"before rebounding afterward."},{"time":573000,"text":"And of course, what we're seeing"},{"time":575000,"text":"is the fact Marc Chagall was a Jewish artist"},{"time":578000,"text":"in Nazi Germany."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580000,"text":"Now these signals"},{"time":582000,"text":"are actually so strong"},{"time":584000,"text":"that we don't need to know that someone was censored."},{"time":587000,"text":"We can actually figure it out"},{"time":589000,"text":"using really basic signal processing."},{"time":591000,"text":"Here's a simple way to do it."},{"time":593000,"text":"Well, a reasonable expectation"},{"time":595000,"text":"is that somebody's fame in a given period of time"},{"time":597000,"text":"should be roughly the average of their fame before"},{"time":599000,"text":"and their fame after."},{"time":601000,"text":"So that's sort of what we expect."},{"time":603000,"text":"And we compare that to the fame that we observe."},{"time":606000,"text":"And we just divide one by the other"},{"time":608000,"text":"to produce something we call a suppression index."},{"time":610000,"text":"If the suppression index is very, very, very small,"},{"time":613000,"text":"then you very well might be being suppressed."},{"time":615000,"text":"If it's very large, maybe you're benefiting from propaganda."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619000,"text":"JM: Now you can actually look at"},{"time":621000,"text":"the distribution of suppression indexes over whole populations."},{"time":624000,"text":"So for instance, here --"},{"time":626000,"text":"this suppression index is for 5,000 people"},{"time":628000,"text":"picked in English books where there's no known suppression --"},{"time":630000,"text":"it would be like this, basically tightly centered on one."},{"time":632000,"text":"What you expect is basically what you observe."},{"time":634000,"text":"This is distribution as seen in Germany --"},{"time":636000,"text":"very different, it's shifted to the left."},{"time":638000,"text":"People talked about it twice less as it should have been."},{"time":641000,"text":"But much more importantly, the distribution is much wider."},{"time":643000,"text":"There are many people who end up on the far left on this distribution"},{"time":646000,"text":"who are talked about 10 times fewer than they should have been."},{"time":649000,"text":"But then also many people on the far right"},{"time":651000,"text":"who seem to benefit from propaganda."},{"time":653000,"text":"This picture is the hallmark of censorship in the book record."}]},{"cues":[{"time":656000,"text":"ELA: So culturomics"},{"time":658000,"text":"is what we call this method."},{"time":660000,"text":"It's kind of like genomics."},{"time":662000,"text":"Except genomics is a lens on biology"},{"time":664000,"text":"through the window of the sequence of bases in the human genome."},{"time":667000,"text":"Culturomics is similar."},{"time":669000,"text":"It's the application of massive-scale data collection analysis"},{"time":672000,"text":"to the study of human culture."},{"time":674000,"text":"Here, instead of through the lens of a genome,"},{"time":676000,"text":"through the lens of digitized pieces of the historical record."},{"time":679000,"text":"The great thing about culturomics"},{"time":681000,"text":"is that everyone can do it."},{"time":683000,"text":"Why can everyone do it?"},{"time":685000,"text":"Everyone can do it because three guys,"},{"time":687000,"text":"Jon Orwant, Matt Gray and Will Brockman over at Google,"},{"time":690000,"text":"saw the prototype of the Ngram Viewer,"},{"time":692000,"text":"and they said, \"This is so fun."},{"time":694000,"text":"We have to make this available for people.\""},{"time":697000,"text":"So in two weeks flat -- the two weeks before our paper came out --"},{"time":699000,"text":"they coded up a version of the Ngram Viewer for the general public."},{"time":702000,"text":"And so you too can type in any word or phrase that you're interested in"},{"time":705000,"text":"and see its n-gram immediately --"},{"time":707000,"text":"also browse examples of all the various books"},{"time":709000,"text":"in which your n-gram appears."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711000,"text":"JM: Now this was used over a million times on the first day,"},{"time":713000,"text":"and this is really the best of all the queries."},{"time":715000,"text":"So people want to be their best, put their best foot forward."},{"time":718000,"text":"But it turns out in the 18th century, people didn't really care about that at all."},{"time":721000,"text":"They didn't want to be their best, they wanted to be their beft."},{"time":724000,"text":"So what happened is, of course, this is just a mistake."},{"time":727000,"text":"It's not that strove for mediocrity,"},{"time":729000,"text":"it's just that the S used to be written differently, kind of like an F."},{"time":732000,"text":"Now of course, Google didn't pick this up at the time,"},{"time":735000,"text":"so we reported this in the science article that we wrote."},{"time":738000,"text":"But it turns out this is just a reminder"},{"time":740000,"text":"that, although this is a lot of fun,"},{"time":742000,"text":"when you interpret these graphs, you have to be very careful,"},{"time":744000,"text":"and you have to adopt the base standards in the sciences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747000,"text":"ELA: People have been using this for all kinds of fun purposes."},{"time":750000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":757000,"text":"Actually, we're not going to have to talk,"},{"time":759000,"text":"we're just going to show you all the slides and remain silent."},{"time":762000,"text":"This person was interested in the history of frustration."},{"time":765000,"text":"There's various types of frustration."},{"time":768000,"text":"If you stub your toe, that's a one A \"argh.\""},{"time":771000,"text":"If the planet Earth is annihilated by the Vogons"},{"time":773000,"text":"to make room for an interstellar bypass,"},{"time":775000,"text":"that's an eight A \"aaaaaaaargh.\""},{"time":777000,"text":"This person studies all the \"arghs,\""},{"time":779000,"text":"from one through eight A's."},{"time":781000,"text":"And it turns out"},{"time":783000,"text":"that the less-frequent \"arghs\""},{"time":785000,"text":"are, of course, the ones that correspond to things that are more frustrating --"},{"time":788000,"text":"except, oddly, in the early 80s."},{"time":791000,"text":"We think that might have something to do with Reagan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":795000,"text":"JM: There are many usages of this data,"},{"time":798000,"text":"but the bottom line is that the historical record is being digitized."},{"time":801000,"text":"Google has started to digitize 15 million books."},{"time":803000,"text":"That's 12 percent of all the books that have ever been published."},{"time":805000,"text":"It's a sizable chunk of human culture."},{"time":808000,"text":"There's much more in culture: there's manuscripts, there newspapers,"},{"time":811000,"text":"there's things that are not text, like art and paintings."},{"time":813000,"text":"These all happen to be on our computers,"},{"time":815000,"text":"on computers across the world."},{"time":817000,"text":"And when that happens, that will transform the way we have"},{"time":820000,"text":"to understand our past, our present and human culture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":824000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}